**Two issues found:**

1. **`text-card/60` opacity modifier won't work** (line 114). In Tailwind v3, the `/60` opacity modifier requires colors defined as bare RGB channels (e.g., `255 255 255`), not as CSS `var()` expressions with hex fallbacks. The date text `text-card/60` will render as fully opaque white instead of 60% opacity. Fix: use a utility like `text-card opacity-60` or define the color as channels.

2. **Hardcoded stroke color** (line 46). The sign-out icon uses `stroke="#F4CB6A"` (gold), but `btn-gold` is now `#FFFFFF`. This is inconsistent ‚Äî the icon will appear gold while the rest of the design system expects white for that role. Should use `stroke="currentColor"` with a `text-btn-gold` class, or update the hex to match.

